title: Drawing, "Project for a carving frame for a back panel of a coach", 1725–50
medium: Brush and gray wash, pen and ink, black chalk
markings: water mark: sun with six rays in circle; L is in the sun; a crown is on top; Below is F
provenance: From the collection of Giovanni Piancastelli; Mr. and Mrs. Edward D. Brandegee
creditline: Museum purchase through gift of various donors and from Eleanor G. Hewitt Fund
description: A wheel and the left half of the frame is shown.  Scrollwork and rocaille.
